tr.td: Transfusion of packed red blood cells, post-op

code.displayName: Transfusion of packed red blood cells, post-op

td.content: Admitted for elective, right Total Knee Replacement (cemented prosthesis). Day 3, developed bilateral basal atelectasis.

The FBC showed high WCC (20.0) and high neutrophils (16.0). Commenced on doxycycline and chest physio. Due to mild anaemia prior to surgery and subsequent operative blood loss, required a blood transfusion of three units. Subsequently made steady progress, regaining good mobility in his knee and is able to mobilise with the aid of a stick. Right knee Xray showed no fracture or dislocation, with the total knee prosthesis well positioned post surgery.

Right knee Xray showed no fracture or dislocation, with the total knee prosthesis well positioned post surgery.
